com.steelypip.powerups.jinxml

Interface Attribute.Iterable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<Attribute>
    Enclosing interface:
    Attribute

    public static interface Attribute.Iterable
extends Iterable<Attribute>
    The Attribute.Iterable class implements the main way to iterate over the attributes of an element and is returned from Element.attributes(). In addition to being an Iterable<Attribute>, it also implements two filtering methods: with(Predicate<Attribute>) and uniqueSelector().

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • with

        default Attribute.Iterable with(Predicate<Attribute> pred)
        Filters an Attribute.Iterable using a predicate to test each attribute in turn. Only the ones that pass the test are included.
        Parameters:
        pred - the test predicate
        Returns:
        a Attribute.Iterable that performs the filtering dynamically

      • uniqueKey

        default Attribute.Iterable uniqueKey()
        Filters a Attribute.Iterable, removing the attributes whose key has already been seen. The effect is that the members each include a different key.
        Returns:
        a Attribute.Iterable that dynamically thins out duplicates.
